-- Scott Ties Record With 64 to Take One-Shot Lead at British Open
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-07-19T12:52:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-19/scott-ties-record-with-64-to-take-one-shot-lead-at-british-open.html
Australian  Adam Scott  shot a record-
tying 64 to hold a one-stroke lead in the opening round of
golf’s British Open.  Scott matched the scoring mark for the Open at Royal Lytham
& St. Annes set by Tom Lehman in the third round in 1996. He’s 6
under par, one shot better than Scotland’s Paul Lawrie and
American Zach Johnson.  Tiger Woods is 3 under through 15 holes, three shots behind
Scott.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  